                </li>
                <li>
                    
                    <p>It would be instructive to compute a table of values as we did in example 1 above (you are urged to do so). 
                        However, we will take a different approach. We note that <m>y = f(x) = \left( \frac{1}{2} \right)^{x} = \frac{1}{2^{x}} = 2^{- x}</m>. If <m>f(x) = 2^{x}</m>, then <m>f( - x) = 2^{- x}</m>. Thus by the graphing principle for <m>f( - x)</m>, we can obtain the graph of <m>y = 2^{- x}</m> by reflecting the graph of <m>y = 2^{x}</m> about the <m>y - \text{axis}</m>.

